Police Minister Bheki Cele has called out City of Cape Town officials for their treatment of Khayelitsha resident, Bulelani Qholani. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Police Minister Bheki Cele has called out City of Cape Town officials for their treatment of Khayelitsha resident, Bulelani Qholani. READ: Govt want answers after eviction of naked man in Cape Town A video of Qholani being dragged out of his shack naked went viral. He tried to return to but he was dragged to the ground. Cele says such treatment of civilians, has never existed, not even during apartheid. "Here we feel there is criminality, that's why the police are part of it and besides that, we were called by the victim himself and the community, there is some criminality here," the minister said.